description:
My work focuses on insights to be found across transgender sociology, public health, psychiatry, history of medicine, cognitive science, the social processes of science, transgender feminism, and human rights, taking an analytic approach that intersects these many perspectives and is guided by the lived experiences of transgender people. The importance of real, concrete support is a guiding value to me, and I'm passionate about community health resources and outreach. I live in Orlando with my family, and work chiefly in technical writing. You can find my earlier articles at http://genderanalysis.net/articles/, and keep an eye out for my new book, "Gender Synthesis: Understanding Gender and Complex Systems in Society", coming in 2017. 

To help support my video series on trans topics, go to https://www.patreon.com/zinniajones. Thanks for stopping by, and remember to subscribe! You can reach me at: zinnia@zinniajones.com

HEY! I'm Pano (yeah that's my real name).

I'm a college student with a passion for film, production and performance. I started on Youtube in 2006 making skateboarding videos with my friends [on a different channel though, good luck finding it ;)], and after a few years break, began filming and posting vlogs in the fall of 2013. 

This channel is really just an outlet for me to be creative and opinionated. I'd like to think I'm a pretty funny and eccentric guy, and love to explore any sort of comedic avenue my brain leads me down. With that said, I've never been one to shy away from more serious topics, and love to share any sort of insight I have into the world of sex, dating and relationships. I'm a member of the LGBTQ+ community (emphasis on the G), and after coming out in high school, immersed myself in a community of other queer Youtubers. I love who I am, and so should you! Above all, I'm just trying my best to be my authentic self.
name: Pano T

description:
Founded by mother-daughter duo Elisa Goodkind and Lily Mandelbaum, StyleLikeU's videos explore how true style is the result of radical self-acceptance.

In The What's Underneath Project, which features shapeshifting models, activists and artists like Girls' Jemima Kirke and OITNB's Lea Delaria, empowered individuals claim self-acceptance by stripping down to open up about style and identity. description:
Her Story looks inside the dating lives of trans & queer women as they navigate the intersections of desire & identity. The plot centers around two trans women in Los Angeles who have given up on love, when suddenly chance encounters give them hope. 

Her Story stars transgender activist Jen Richards who is currently featured in E!’s I Am Cait and wrote the controversial cover story for August's Advocate Magazine about the inner workings of the Trans Movement.  The series also features accomplished trans entrepreneur and actor Angelica Ross and writer/actor Laura Zak, star of the hit web series #Hashtag.

Jen Richards and Laura Zak are co-writers and co-executive producers on the series, with award-winning filmmaker Sydney Freeland (Drunktown’s Finest) directing. It's Executive produced by playwright and activist Eve Ensler, and Katherine Fisher of Speed of Joy Productions.
